    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>baking paper </strong>and a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>then add the <strong>turkey joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>(leave the string on!)</p><p>Slide <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sage leaves</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) under the string of the turkey joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and top with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> knobs of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Cover the turkey with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 35 min or until it's cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
